  "issue_number": 264,
  "issue_title": "Feature: add local model evaluation runner",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\nAfter fixtures exist, TouchPilot needs a repeatable way to evaluate local model outputs without relying on manual review.\n\n## Proposed behavior\nAdd a small evaluation runner that reads the committed fixtures and reports pass/fail counts for deterministic expectations.\n\n## Goal to reach\nA developer can run one command and see whether local model routing contracts still pass the minimal eval set.\n\n## Minimal scope\n- Read the fixture format added for Milestone 8.\n- Evaluate current deterministic/local-model command output where supported.\n- Print total cases, passed cases, failed cases, and failure details.\n- Add a focused test or Gradle task hook if it fits the existing test style.\n\n## Out of scope\n- Training models.\n- Accuracy dashboards.\n- Device/emulator live tests.\n- UI reporting.\n\n## User workflow\nA maintainer runs the eval before and after model/router changes to compare behavior.\n\n## Local-first impact\nThis makes local model quality measurable inside the repository.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\nThe runner must not call network services or execute Android actions. It should evaluate outputs only.\n\n## Alternatives considered\nManual spot checks are too inconsistent for model-quality work.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-16T03:25:18.000Z",
